"title": "6182: ignorance, and human situation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6182",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Ignorance is part of the human condition: as finite creatures, human knowledge is incomplete, but human beings can trust God, whose knowledge is complete, to guide their steps.</p>\n<h2>Ignorance of God</h2>\n<h3>Finite human beings cannot know God completely</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl11:5\">ECC 11:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:1-Job38:7\">JOB 38:1–38:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl3:11\">ECC 3:11</a></p>\n<h3>This ignorance will be dispelled at Jesus Christ's return</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:9-1Cor13:12\">1CO 13:9–13:12</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Ignorance of the future</h2>\n<h3>Human beings are ignorant of future events</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:7-Eccl8:8\">ECC 8:7–8:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl3:22\">ECC 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:12\">ECC 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl10:14\">ECC 10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl11:2\">ECC 11:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl11:6\">ECC 11:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:22\">ACT 20:22</a></p>\n<h3>Human beings are ignorant of the time of Jesus Christ's return</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:32-Mark13:36\">MRK 13:32–13:36</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:36-Matt24:44\">MAT 24:36–24:44</a></p>\n<h3>Presumptious plans should therefore be avoided</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:13-Jas4:16\">JAS 4:13–4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps39:6\">PSA 39:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:1\">PRO 27:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:16-Luke12:21\">LUK 12:16–12:21</a></p>\n<h3>God's guidance is essential</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:24\">PRO 20:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:21\">PRO 19:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:23\">JER 10:23</a></p>\n<h2>Ignorance of doctrinal matters</h2>\n<h3>Within the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:13-1Thess4:18\">1TH 4:13–4:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:1-1Cor10:10\">1CO 10:1–10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:1-1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:1–12:11</a></p>\n<h3>God has established teachers to combat ignorance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28\">1CO 12:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11-Eph4:13\">EPH 4:11–4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:13\">1TI 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17\">1TI 5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:16-2Tim3:17\">2TI 3:16–3:17</a></p>\n<h2>Ignorance may lead to death</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov9:17-Prov9:18\">PRO 9:17–9:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:19\">PRO 4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:21-Prov7:23\">PRO 7:21–7:23</a></p>",
